        "can_recover": false,
        "can_see_hidden_post": false,
        "can_unaccept_answer": false,
        "can_view_edit_history": true,
        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>The \u201cnew\u201d startpage (not the generatorpage) is deeply disappointing \u2014 in fact, it feels like a major step backward.<br>\nIt\u2019s hard to believe that a UI designer approved this layout; whoever made these decisions should seriously reconsider their approach to usability and user experience.<br>\nThe single-page structure is frustrating and impractical. Why isn\u2019t there at least an option to use a paged layout \u2014 something every well-designed interface allows? And why can\u2019t generators be opened in a new window with a simple left-click?<br>\nPerformance is another major issue. Recalculations after parameter changes take ages. It almost feels like the interface was designed to waste time. Adding more delays would only mean we could finish not just making coffee but baking a whole cake before updates appear.<br>\nAlso, changes to parameters should update automatically, without requiring an extra click on \u201cGenerate.\u201d<br>\nConsidering how many talented programmers share their outstanding work here, it\u2019s hard to believe there\u2019s not at least one great UI or web designer around. Why not ask some of these professionals for input?<br>\nMajor UI Refresh? my \u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u2026 <img src=\"https://forum.bambulab.com/images/emoji/twitter/face_vomiting.png?v=14\" title=\":face_vomiting:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":face_vomiting:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
